'''Director of Imperial Intelligence''', also known as the '''Internal Security Director''', was a title held by the leader of [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] . The position was considered a successor to that of [[Director of the Senate Bureau of Intelligence|Director]] of the [[Senate Bureau of Intelligence/Legends|Senate Bureau of Intelligence]], for when [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] established the Galactic Empire [[19 BBY/Legends|three years after]] the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]], the bureau became Imperial Intelligence. Under the Empire, this post&mdash;considered a part and in command of the [[Ubiqtorate/Legends|Ubiqtorate]]&mdash;was the highest level of command within Imperial Intelligence, one of much power and prestige.

The post is known to have been held by only three persons: [[Armand Isard/Legends|Armand Isard]], who was appointed to his position under the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] by then-[[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] Palpatine, [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]] [[Cronal]], who filled in as an interim director after Armand's daughter [[Ysanne Isard]] executed her father, and eventually Ysanne Isard who was appointed in his place by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] Palpatine after Cronal's exile to the Outer Rim. This post would eventually come to command the whole of the Empire after the death of Palpatine and his [[Grand Vizier/Legends|Grand Vizier]] [[Sate Pestage/Legends|Sate Pestage]], though the position was never meant for such authority.

